# Basic commands

Commands to be used in User EXEC mode

enable -> switches from User EXEC to Privilge EXEC.



Commands to be used in Privilege EXEC mode

configure terminal -> Switches from Privilege access to Global configuration mode.

hostname -> Allows a device's hostname to be changed

enable password -> Protects Privilege EXEC access
service password-encryption -> Makes the enable password unreadable

enable password secret -> Protects the Privilege EXEC access using MD5 encryption.

show running-confiuguration -> Shows the current active configuration of the router

show startup-config -> Shows the configuration that will be loaded during the next boot of the router

write, write memory or copy running-config startu-config -> Allow to save the running configuration to be saved into the startup configuration


